VALUES ('64c4b24b-52ba-4d3c-ae43-55cf47da5784', 'Based on the texts, how would the author of Text 2 most likely respond to the claim in Text 1 that the printing press was the chief engine of the Reformation?', 'Text 1
The printing press was the chief engine of the Reformation. By mass-producing pamphlets and Bibles, it spread reformers'' ideas faster than authorities could suppress them. Without this machine, the movement would have stayed a quarrel among scholars.

Text 2
Presses printed in Latin and German alike, yet the Reformation took hold only where preachers and reading circles carried the message into daily speech. The technology mattered, but ideas spread through the patient work of people willing to argue them aloud in town and church.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"The printing press slowed the spread of reformist ideas.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"No evidence; Text 2 says technology mattered, never that it slowed things."},{"id":"B","text":"The movement spread mainly through people who argued the ideas aloud, not the press alone.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: Text 2 credits the patient work of people arguing ideas aloud in town and church."},{"id":"C","text":"Pamphlets were the only way ideas could reach common people.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Restates Text 1''s emphasis, contradicting Text 2."},{"id":"D","text":"The Reformation remained merely a quarrel among scholars.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Contradicts Text 2, which describes ideas reaching towns and churches."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Step 1 — Find Text 2''s claim
Text 2 argues ideas spread {{yellow:through the patient work of people willing to argue them aloud in town and church}}.
Step 2 — Apply to Text 1
Because Text 2 highlights human preachers and reading circles, it would qualify Text 1''s claim that the press itself was the chief engine.
Distractor analysis:
- A: No evidence—Text 2 grants technology mattered.
- C: Restates Text 1''s press-centered view.
- D: Contradicts Text 2''s picture of ideas reaching daily speech.', 'What does Text 2 say carried the message into daily speech?', 'Craft and Structure', 'Cross-Text Connections', 'reading_writing', 'craft', 'CTC', NULL, 'easy', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"scholaris_ai_v1","model":"gemma-4-26b-a4b-it","original":true,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
